==French ==
===Etymology===
From Frankish ''*markôn''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/maʀʃe/}}

===Verb===
'''marcher'''

# to [[walk]].
#: ''Il '''marche''' au milieu de la rue.'' - He walks on the middle of the street.
# to [[work]], to function
#: ''Cet ordinateur ne  '''marche''' pas.'' - This computer does not work.
# to [[agree]].
#: ''Ça '''marche'''.'' - I agree.
# to [[believe]].
#: ''Il '''marche'''.'' - He believes my joke.
#: ''Il m'a fait '''marcher'''.'' - He makes me believe his joke.

